# Backend Configuration Module

## PURPOSE
Configuration files for database, environment variables, and app settings.

## CONTAINS
- database.js: Database connection configuration
- stripe.js: Stripe API configuration
- jwt.js: JWT token configuration
- env.example: Example environment variables

## ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
- NODE_ENV: development | production
- PORT: Server port (default: 3000)
- DATABASE_URL: MongoDB/PostgreSQL connection string
- JWT_SECRET: Secret key for JWT signing
- JWT_EXPIRE: Token expiration time
- STRIPE_SECRET_KEY: Stripe secret key
- STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET: Stripe webhook secret
- FRONTEND_URL: Extension URL for CORS

## REFERENCES
- Parent: /backend/.windsurf
- Root: /.windsurf
- Used by: /backend/server.js, /backend/routes/*

## RULES
- Never commit .env file to git
- Use strong random secrets
- Different configs for dev/prod
- Validate all env vars on startup
